The variable $X$ is normally distributed with parameters $a=2$ and $\sigma=3$. Calculate the following probabilities:
a) $1 \leqslant X \leqslant 2 ;$ 
b) $X \geqslant 2$;
c) $|X-2| \leqslant 3 ;$
d) $X \leqslant -1$;
e) $|X-2| \leqslant 9$.

Compare which of the numbers is greater:
a) $\sqrt{2}+\sqrt{3}$ or $\sqrt{11}$;
b) $\sqrt{6}+2 \sqrt{7}$ or $\sqrt{10}+\sqrt{21}$;
c) $\sqrt{11}$ or $5-\sqrt[3]{5}$.

An L-shaped region is formed by attaching two  $2$  by  $5$  rectangles to adjacent sides of a  $2$  by  $2$  square as shown below.
[asy] size(6cm);
draw((0,0)--(7,0)--(7,2)--(2,2)--(2,7)--(0,7)--cycle);
real eps = 0.45;
draw(box( (0,0), (eps,eps) ));
draw(box( (7,0), (7-eps,eps) ));
draw(box( (7,2), (7-eps,2-eps) ));
draw(box( (0,7), (eps,7-eps) ));
draw(box( (2,7), (2-eps,7-eps) ));
label(" $7$ ", (0,3.5), dir(180));
label(" $7$ ", (3.5,0), dir(270));
label(" $2$ ", (7,1), dir(0));
label(" $5$ ", (4.5,2), dir(90));
label(" $5$ ", (2,4.5), dir(0));
label(" $2$ ", (1,7), dir(90));
[/asy]
The resulting shape has an area of  $24$  square units.  How many ways are there to tile this shape with  $2$  by  $1$  dominos (each of which may be placed horizontally or vertically)?

Let \( p_{1}, p_{2}, p_{3}, \ldots \) be the prime numbers listed in increasing order, and let \( 0 < x_{0} < 1 \) be a real number between 0 and 1. For each positive integer \( k \), define

\[ x_{k}=\left\{
    \begin{array}{ll}
    0 & \text { if } x_{k-1}=0, \\
    \left\{ \frac{p_{k}}{x_{k-1}} \right\} & \text { if } x_{k-1} \neq 0,
    \end{array}
\right. \]

where \( \{x\} \) denotes the fractional part of \( x \). Find, with proof, all \( x_{0} \) satisfying \( 0 < x_{0} < 1 \) for which the sequence \( x_{0}, x_{1}, x_{2}, \ldots \) eventually becomes 0.
